theorem Topology.closureInteriorClosure_eq_closure_of_P3
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hP3 : Topology.P3 (A := A)) :
    closure (interior (closure A)) = closure A := by
  -- `closure (interior (closure A))` is contained in `closure A`
  have h₁ : closure (interior (closure A)) ⊆ closure A := by
    have : interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A := interior_subset
    exact closure_mono this
  -- From `P3`, we get the reverse inclusion after taking closures
  have h₂ : closure A ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) := by
    have : (A : Set X) ⊆ interior (closure A) := hP3
    exact closure_mono this
  exact subset_antisymm h₁ h₂

theorem Topology.P3_implies_P2_of_isClosed {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA_closed : IsClosed A) (hP3 : Topology.P3 (A := A)) :
    Topology.P2 (A := A) := by
  have hA_open : IsOpen A :=
    (Topology.P3_iff_isOpen_of_isClosed (A := A) hA_closed).1 hP3
  exact Topology.P2_of_isOpen (A := A) hA_open
